On 11 May 2025. State, country: River Nile, Sudan. Text: Sudanese media reports drone attack on Atbara in River Nile state. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: N/A

On 01 July 2025. Country: Sudan. Text: Sudan's rebel RSF forms political alliance with Sudan People’s Liberation Movement-North and others to govern areas under its control, mainly in Darfur. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: politics. Tag: government
---
On 24 June 2025. Country: Sudan. State: South Darfur. Town: Nyala Janoub. Text: On 24 June 2025, 2 RSF groups clashed in Taiyba Al Nile market in Nyala (Nyala Janoub, South Darfur). Many civilians were wounded. Number of fatalities: 0.  Opposing sides: Rebel group-Rebel group. Actor 1: Rapid Support Forces. Actor 2: Rapid Support Forces. Type of event: Battles (Armed clash)..
---
On 27 April 2025. State, country: White Nile, Sudan. Text: Report: Sudan's Rapid Support Forces launch drone strikes on Sudanese military position in Arshkool area of White Nile State, Al Jazeera reports citing military source. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: Rapid Support Forces
---
On 25 June 2025. Country: Sudan. State: Blue Nile. Town: Bau. Text: On 25 June 2025, SAF clashed with SFA (coded as RSF and SPLM-N-Abdelaziz) in Baldugu (Bau, Blue Nile) and regained control over the area (SPLM-N initially gained control of the area around 15 November 2024 - coded separately), with SAF drone strikes being reported. RSF withdrew to South Sudan. Casualties unknown. Number of fatalities: 0.  Opposing sides: State forces-Rebel group. Actor 1: Military Forces of Sudan (2019-). Actor 2: SFA: Sudan Founding Alliance (associated with: Rapid Support Forces; SPLM-N-Abdelaziz: Sudan People's Liberation Movement (North) (Abdelaziz al-Hilu faction)). Type of event: Battles (Government regains territory)..

On 29 June 2025. State, country: Al Jazirah, Sudan. Text: Sudan's Bank of Khartoum reopens its branch in Hasahisa, al-Jazirah state, following months-long suspension imposed by security situation. Severity (from 1 to 4): 1. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: Bank of Khartoum
---
On 12 April 2025. State, country: North Darfur, Sudan. Text: Sudanese local media reports continuing clashes in Zamzam Camp south of El Fasher between RSF paramilitary and government forces. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: NGO
---
On 23 April 2025. State, country: North Darfur, Sudan. Text: Sudan's warring military factions continue fighting in multiple parts of el-Fasher, Al-Arabiya reports. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: N/A
---
On 17 April 2025. State, country: North Darfur, Sudan. Text: Sudanese media reports new fighting between RSF and Sudanese armed forces in the northeast of El Fasher, Sudan. Severity (from 1 to 4): 2. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: N/A
---
On 23 April 2025. State, country: North Darfur, Sudan. Text: RSF militia forces shell Abu Shouk camp and the Al-Quba and Al-Nasr neighborhoods of El Fasher, Al Jazeera reports citing Sudanese military sources. Severity (from 1 to 4): 2. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: N/A
---
On 29 April 2025. State, country: White Nile, Sudan. Text: Sudan's rebel RSF targets army command in town of Kosti with drone strike, Al-Jazeera reports, citing unidentified military source. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: N/A
---
On 20 May 2025. State, country: Khartoum, Sudan. Text: Editor's note: Military sources have told Al Jazeera that Khartoum State, Sudan, has been recaptured in full from the RSF militia by the army. A short while ago an official said that the Sudan army was "close" to recapturing all of Khartoum State, but there was also still fighting reported in Omdurman. We will update when we have a citable source confirming the army is claiming to have retaken the whole state. -Sarah. Severity (from 1 to 4): 1. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: Rapid Support Forces
---
On 13 April 2025. State, country: North Darfur, Sudan. Text: Rebel group Sudan Liberation Movement calls on army for help in el-Fasher, Darfur, where paramilitary bombing continues, including in nearby displacement camps. Severity (from 1 to 4): 2. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: immigration
---
On 04 June 2025. State, country: Northern, Sudan. Text: Update: Sudanese media reports renewed roadblocking by protesters in Wadi Halfa, threats of escalation including disruption of mining operations. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: mining
---
On 08 May 2025. State, country: White Nile, Sudan. Text: Al Jazeera reports explosions near oil depots in Kosti, Sudan; no further details yet available. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: energy
---
On 11 April 2025. State, country: North Darfur, Sudan. Text: Editor's note: One local journalist is reporting, without citing sources, that the paramilitary group RSF launched new strikes in the Sudanese city of El Fasher, prompting army to respond with artillery. Clashes between the group and armed forces have continued to escalate this week after RSF reportedly captured Um Kadadah, a key town on the road to El Fasher. The Sudanese military said earlier that at least 20 people have been killed during RSF paramilitary shelling in the city. We are continuing to follow the situation closely. -Jessica. Severity (from 1 to 4): 1. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: N/A
---
On 05 June 2025. State, country: North Darfur, Sudan. Text: At least 14 people killed, others injured after RSF militia attack camp in El Fasher, Sudan, according to officials. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: N/A
---
On 05 May 2025. State, country: Red Sea, Sudan. Text: Editor's note: We are aware of images circulating on social media of a large fire burning at multiple oil depots in Port Sudan, Sudan. The attack has not yet been reported on by Sudanese media, and the cause of the fires is still unclear. The fires come just one day after a series of RSF paramilitary drone strikes in the city, which were the first of the country's two year civil war. We are watching our sources for more information. - Owen. Severity (from 1 to 4): 1. Theme: N/A. Tag: fires
---
On 13 April 2025. State, country: North Darfur, Sudan. Text: Sudan’s paramilitary RSF claims control over Zamzam camp south of embattled el-Fasher amid reports of clashes and large-scale displacement. Severity (from 1 to 4): 5. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: immigration
---
On 03 June 2025. State, country: North Darfur, Sudan. Text: WFP and UNICEF now say five members were killed, several more injured in earlier attack on aid convoy near Al Koma, Sudan; multiple trucks burned. Severity (from 1 to 4): 3. Theme: war & conflict. Tag: United Nations
